data.title: "I Had A Great Time" | Utah Honors Former All-Star Carlos Boozer
data.meta_description: It was a chant that sent shivers down the spines of many people at Vivint Arena on Friday night. "Booooooooooozzzzzzzzzzzzz" Former Jazz big man Carlos Boozer was back in the snowy mountains of Salt Lake City as Utah honored one of its greats. A two-time all-star and all-NBA selectee in his six seasons with the Jazz, Boozer was given a standing ovation by the Utah faithful when he was introduced to the crowd during the third quarter against the Phoenix Suns.
